  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nA simple contract with withdraw functions that use the `transfer()` function works normally on L1 but fails on Optimism.\r\nAt first, without hardcoding the `gasLimit`, the tests fails with `code=UNPREDICTABLE_GAS_LIMIT`.\r\nAs suggested on the Discord channel, I set a `gasLimit` for the deploy and each function call. This way the transaction simply fails.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. clone the repo at https://github.com/moreira-a/optimism-test\r\n2. Run `npx hardhat test`. It works normally\r\n3. Start a Optimism development node\r\n4. Run `npx hardhat --network optimism test`. It fails\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nA simple contract like this should work normally on L2\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\nWithout hardcoded `gasLimit`:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/70960269/131689767-fc998f95-be84-4672-a269-9dd80eb0f6fc.png)\r\n\r\nWith hardcoded `gasLimit`:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/70960269/131690077-43371c96-2745-4b41-b7f1-3502bf494a97.png)\r\n\r\n**System Specs:**\r\n - OS: Ubuntu 18.04\r\n \r\n**Additional context**\r\nThread on Optimism Discord about this https://discord.com/channels/667044843901681675/667044844366987296/881710177047425054",
